{"id": 78, "ts": 1778839335.5245984, "event": "public_discussion_message", "round": 2, "agent": "agent_2", "message": "Based on the complete set of explicit information we have, the candidates compare as follows:\n**Candidate A** \u2013 Strengths: anticipates dangerous situations, sees complex connections, excellent spatial vision, very good leadership qualities.\nWeaknesses: regarded as a show\u2011off, not open to new ideas, unorganized, struggles with criticism. No data on reliability, calmness under pressure, or teamwork/communication.\n**Candidate B** \u2013 Strengths: 100\u202f% reliable, stays calm in a crisis, good at assessing weather, excellent computer skills.\nWeaknesses: relatively weak memory for numbers, makes nasty remarks about colleagues, described as uncooperative/grumpy, which undermines crew cohesion. No further technical competence beyond weather assessment and computers.\n**Candidate C** \u2013 Strengths: very conscientious (reliable), handles stress very well (calm under pressure), makes correct decisions quickly, understands complicated technology, excellent attention skills, creates a positive atmosphere with his crew.\nWeaknesses: difficulty communicating ideas, regarded as egocentric, not very willing to pursue further education. These issues are noted but are partially mitigated by his ability to foster a good crew atmosphere.\n**Candidate D** \u2013 Strengths: responds adequately to unexpected events (calm under pressure), takes responsibility seriously, solves problems extremely well, can concentrate very well.\nWeaknesses: moody, hot\u2011tempered, regarded as a loner, arrogant, weak leadership, seen as a know\u2011it\u2011all. No explicit evidence of reliability, technical competence in navigation or systems, or teamwork/communication style.\nWhen weighing the criteria for a long\u2011distance pilot\u2014reliability, technical and cognitive competence, calmness under pressure, sound decision\u2011making, and crew cooperation\u2014Candidate\u202fC provides the most balanced and safety\u2011critical profile. His reliability, stress handling, rapid correct decision\u2011making, and technical understanding directly address the core requirements, while his communication shortcomings are the only notable gap and are partially offset by his positive crew atmosphere.\nGiven that no additional positive data exists for Candidates\u202fA or\u202fD, and Candidate\u202fB\u2019s interpersonal attitude poses a clear risk to crew dynamics, Candidate\u202fC remains the strongest overall fit for the high\u2011responsibility international flights.\n**Vote:** Candidate C\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_2\", \"vote\": \"Candidate C\"}"}
